This is the problem with youth in America today.<br>
<br>
There is a HUGE difference between &quot;spanking&quot; and &quot;beating&quot;, yet our culture has blurred the line so much that most parents are afraid to spank their children.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry, but this is a VERY bad thing.  Younger children will NOT learn proper behavior without a certain level of PHYSICAL punishment.<br>
<br>
How do you teach a 4 year old not to touch something hot? Do you explain it to them and hope they comprehend? or do you smack their lil hand when they repeatedly reach for it?  Trust me, the hand smack works wuch better, and is far less painful (and therefore KINDER) than the burn the child would get if they didn't get the point of your talk.<br>
<br>
As children get older, spankings become less necissary.  They become capable of advanced reasoning, and more &quot;adult&quot; methods of punishment become preferable.  Nothing saddens me more than seeing some frazzeled mother screaming at the top of her lungs at some poor child because she's afraid that if she spanks the child she'll lose it.<br>
<br>
Children can tune out screaming fairly easily.  Also, it demeans the parent, is childish to begin with, and has no lasting effect.  I never yell at children.  I treat them with respect and as equals, but they know if the cross the line, they will get their lil buts spanked.  It will hurt.  It won't leave bruises or in any way be &quot;a beating&quot; but trust me, my children are some of the most well behaved children around, and I rarely have to discipline them.  Why? because they learned at an early age that disobedience ment a very real punishment.<br>
<br>
Spare the rod, spoil the child.  It's a valid motto, and today's youth, in general, are living proof of just what happens when you don't use physical discipline at a young age to set the foundation for acceptable behavior. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiceweaselx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ice Weasel X</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 543<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/02 11:18:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3406.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> I'm of the opinion that spanking a child's butt with an open hand or flat paddle (such as Louisiana schools used to utilize) can be used without being abusive. &nbsp;Slapping (Ever see someone with a sore neck from being slapped? &nbsp;I have), shaking (hard enough to injure joints), using a belt wrapped around your fist or as a whip, kicking, throwing, burning, cutting... those are all methods of physical punishment I find highly offensive.<br>
