<br>
My brother on the other hand wasn't so &quot;easy&quot; to discipline.  I remember there being times when he was spanked for this that or the other thing.  I never thought of it as abuse and neither did he.  My younger brothers and sisters get spanked when they do something way out of line.  But it's just as was said earlier, when they get older it's far less frequent that they need to be disciplined in that fashion because they learned when they were younger.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, we grew up next to this family that doesn't have any idea what &quot;discipline&quot; is.  They've never spanked their kids.  The worse they get is sent to their room (which, as the original poster stated, has a TV, all their toys, etc.)  Oh boo hoo....like the kids are gonna care.  These are the most obnoxious, rude, and ill-mannered kids I think I have ever known.<br>
<br>
I definitely think society is lacking in their discipline and punishment for children.  Unfortunately social services seems to go after the parents who had their kids complain because they got spanked the night before rather than those that legitimately beat their kids and scare them into silence.  And if not them, you hear from some people all the time about how horrible it is if you spank your children and omg how could you do that!  *sigh*<br>
