And a good spanking would show these children that their actions have real consequences.  If my kids where to ever destroy someone elses property, they would most definately get a spanking for it.  Then they'd also have to go face-to-face and apologize to the person.  Then they'd also have to do whatever they could to replace/repair the destruction.  (Be it doing chores to earn the money to fix the mailbox, or working to helping re-plant the flowers or whatever, the situation would dictate)<br>
